<h2>Style guide</h2><p>These rules apply to all interior texts and articles. </p><div class="table styleguide-table"><div class="tr table-header"><div class="td"></div><div class="td"><h6>No</h6></div><div class="td"><h6>Yes</h6></div></div><div class="tr"><div class="td"><p>The brand name — Dodo Pizza — should be used without quotation marks.</p><p>Both words should should be capitalized.</p></div><div class="td"><p>We work at “Dodo pizza”</p></div><div class="td"><p>We work at Dodo Pizza</p></div></div><div class="tr"><div class="td"><p>When addressing the audience use <em>We</em></p><p>Our customers in stores should be called guests. </p></div><div class="td"><p>I’ll try to help you</p><p>Customers love our coffee</p></div><div class="td"><p>We’ll try to help you </p><p>Our guests love our coffee</p></div></div><div class="tr table-header"><div class="td"></div><div class="td"><h6>No</h6></div><div class="td"><h6>Yes</h6></div></div><div class="tr"><div class="td"><p>Capitalize product and holiday names and names of organisations. No quotation marks.</p></div><div class="td"><p>We have improved “ranch pizza”</p><p>Merry christmas!</p></div><div class="td"><p>We have improved Ranch pizza</p><p>Merry Christmas!</p></div></div><div class="tr"><div class="td"><p>Avoid using strong words like “wrong”, “forbidden”, etc.</p></div><div class="td"><p>Tearing lettuce leaves with hands is forbidden. </p></div><div class="td"><p>Don’t tear lettuce leaves with hands.</p></div></div><div class="tr table-header"><div class="td"></div><div class="td"><h6>No</h6></div><div class="td"><h6>Yes</h6></div></div><div class="tr"><div class="td"><p>Use Emoji only in social media </p><p>They shouldn’t substitute words.</p><p>They can’t be used as list markers</p><p>Use no more than three in a row</p><p>Or better yet don’t use them at all</p></div><div class="td"><p>🎉🎉🎉 Try  our new Pepperoni 🍕 with jalapeno! 💣💥 It contains: </p><p>📌 Pepperoni</p><p>📌 Marinara sauce</p><p>📌 Mozzarella</p><p>📌 Oregano 🙌</p></div><div class="td"><p>Try our new Pepperoni with jalapeno! It contains pepperoni, marinara sauce, mozzarella, and oregano. </p></div></div></div><div class="article-footer"><div class="links"><span>Tags:</span><a class="js-tag-link" href="everything.html#brand">Brand</a><a class="js-tag-link" href="everything.html#language">Language</a></div></div>